    h2 # art style
    p Several options:
    ol(type="A")
      li
        p 1:1 scale 3D
        div(class="centered")
          img(src="/images/stories/not-top/mockup-A1.jpg", style='max-width:100%; max-height:400px;')
        p Easier for player to see into the distance, wayfinding is encouraged. Barely no abstractions. AI buddy behavior has been attempted many times in AAA games, and it can easily look bad. Extensive content creation required, very easy to break immersion with imperfections or inconsistencies. Examples: FFXV, Breath of the Wild.
        div(class="centered")
          img(src="/images/stories/not-top/mockup-A2.jpg", style='max-width:100%; max-height:440px;')

      li
        p PSX-era abstracted 3D
        div(class="centered")
          img(src="/images/stories/not-top/mockup-B.jpg", style='max-width:100%; max-height:350px;')
        p Abstracts content, "easier" to develop. Can be combined with style A for specific points of interest, or maybe through explicit player input (would require procedurally-generated detailed view?). Exploration elements need to be clearer in the abstracted world. Dialogue triggering and gameplay elements can cheat.
      
      li
        p SNES-era top down map, close-up inside POIs
        div(class="centered")
          img(src="/images/stories/not-top/mockup-C1.jpg", style='max-width:100%; max-height:400px;')
        p Different style of exploration, it's no longer possible to place points of interest in the distance to incite interest. Easier to develop. Once the player understands the language, it's harder to break immersion as long as elements stay consistent with the abstractions they represent.
          br
          | Similar to styles A+B, close-up view can be triggered at Points of Interest or through player controls.
        div(class="centered")
          img(src="/images/stories/not-top/mockup-C2.jpg", style='max-width:100%; max-height:380px;')
      li
        p Black and white contour rendering
        div(class="centered")
          img(src="/images/stories/not-top/mockup-D.jpg", style='max-width:100%; max-height:440px;')
        p Can retain wayfinding benefits of style A, while still abstracting content and reducing the asset production efforts. It'd likely require a good amount of investigation and iteration to find the right combination of style vs playability, since visibility and clarity are not immediate with this style. There may not be as much literature available to help solve issues.